#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-
"""
Copyright (C) 2009-2015, Markus Hubig <mhubig@imko.de>
"""

from os import getenv
import pymssql

DB_USER = getenv('SAGE_DB_USER', 'sa')
DB_PASW = getenv('SAGE_DB_PASW', '')
DB_HOST = getenv('SAGE_DB_HOST', '192.168.1.30')
DB_NAME = getenv('SAGE_DB_NAME', 'OLIMKOGmbH')

if __name__ == "__main__":
    conn = pymssql.connect(DB_HOST, DB_USER, DB_PASW, 'OLIMKOGmbH')
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    with open('offene_positionen.sql') as query:
        sql = query.read()
        cursor.execute(sql)

    row = cursor.fetchone()
    while row:
        print(row)
        row = cursor.fetchone()

    conn.close()
